  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "ADMIN ACCOUNTS MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>As an Admin Accounts Manager, you will be responsible for managing and maintaining financial records, processing invoices, handling payroll, and ensuring compliance with financial regulations. You will work closely with the finance team to support the company’s financial processes and procedures.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Manage accounts payable and receivable processes</li><li>Maintain accurate financial records and ledgers</li><li>Process invoices and monitor payments</li><li>Handle payroll and ensure timely payments</li><li>Reconcile bank statements and financial discrepancies</li><li>Prepare financial reports and statements</li><li>Assist in budget preparation and financial planning</li><li>Ensure compliance with financial regulations and policies</li><li>Provide administrative support to the finance team</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Proven experience in a similar financial administration role</li><li>Strong understanding of accounting principles and financial regulations</li><li>Attention to detail and accuracy in financial record-keeping</li><li>Excellent organizational and time-management skills</li><li>Proficiency in financial software and tools</li></ul>",
